42
00:03:30.252 --> 00:03:34.213
A priest. a rabbi and an imam are
all fishing together on a boat

43
00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:35.840
in the middle of a lake.

44
00:03:35.841 --> 00:03:39.010
And the priest realizes he left
his fishing rod in the car.

45
00:03:39.011 --> 00:03:42.889
So the priest. he turns to his colleagues.
and he says. "Hey. I'll be right back."

46
00:03:42.890 --> 00:03:46.851
He gets out of the boat. He walks
across the water to the beach.

47
00:03:46.852 --> 00:03:51.939
He goes to the car. He gets back across
the water and gets into the boat.

48
00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:55.443
The rabbi is amazed. The
priest just walked on water.

49
00:03:55.444 --> 00:03:58.696
About 30 minutes later. the imam
says. "I have to go to the toilet."

50
00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:03.993
So. he stands up. steps out of the boat.
walks across the water to the beach.

51
00:04:03.994 --> 00:04:07.747
finds the nearest men's room. walks back
across the water and gets into the boat.

52
00:04:07.748 --> 00:04:09.916
The rabbi stares dumbfounded.

53
00:04:09.917 --> 00:04:13.461
But he thinks. "Well. my faith
is at least as strong as theirs."

54
00:04:13.462 --> 00:04:16.338
So. he says. "I'm
a little thirsty.

55
00:04:16.339 --> 00:04:19.509
There's a snack bar over there
on the beach. Excuse me."

56
00:04:19.510 --> 00:04:23.846
He stands up. puts his feet in the
water. Splash. Sinks like a stone.

57
00:04:23.847 --> 00:04:25.932
- And then he...
- I told you that joke. That's my joke.

58
00:04:25.933 --> 00:04:27.391
I love that joke.

59
00:04:27.392 --> 00:04:30.144
And it's "refreshment
stand." not "snack bar."

60
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:33.606
Are you sure you wanna make
jokes your first day as a rabbi?

61
00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:36.275
Yeah. Well. first of all. rabbis
are supposed to tell jokes.

62
00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:39.403
And secondly. it's a perfect
description of the job.

63
00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:43.157
That's what I'm doing. I'm helping people
find a way through difficult passages.

64
00:04:43.158 --> 00:04:44.617
That's what I do at the center.

65
00:04:44.618 --> 00:04:47.119
How are you helping
people with no homes

66
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:50.540
by sending them to other places
where they have no homes?

67
00:04:50.541 --> 00:04:54.210
Dad. it's not their fault they don't
have homes. It's... They were...

68
00:04:54.211 --> 00:04:55.712
I gotta get this.

69
00:04:56.380 --> 00:04:58.297
- Hello. Junior.
- They were displaced.

70
00:04:58.298 --> 00:04:59.465
Are you there yet?

71
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:01.384
Marshall. how long
has it been like this?

72
00:05:01.385 --> 00:05:03.345
I can barely
breathe in this air.

73
00:05:05.764 --> 00:05:08.183
So much smoke from the looting.

74
00:05:09.601 --> 00:05:14.314
No. Ma. There's no looting. That's
