long as our basic needs are guaranteed.

145
00:09:26.900 --> 00:09:29.694
Can you elaborate on
the term "basic needs"?

146
00:09:29.695 --> 00:09:31.905
Unlimited refuge in Europe?

147
00:09:34.199 --> 00:09:36.952
Water.

148
00:09:37.953 --> 00:09:39.453
We'd like access
to state of the art

149
00:09:39.454 --> 00:09:42.206
desalinization and
purification technology.

150
00:09:42.207 --> 00:09:43.916
And what do you
mean by "access"?

151
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:47.504
The patents and designs developed
by Alpha Hydro Solutions.

152
00:09:48.255 --> 00:09:52.884
You think Nicholas Bilton is
going to just give you his patents

153
00:09:52.885 --> 00:09:54.678
because we ask nicely?

154
00:09:55.345 --> 00:09:58.181
Okay. Drought leads
to instability.

155
00:09:58.182 --> 00:10:02.852
Look at Sudan in '24.
Cape Town in '27.

156
00:10:02.853 --> 00:10:04.937
Look at the west.
Argentina. 2033...

157
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:08.024
Look here. We have made
such progress in the region.

158
00:10:08.025 --> 00:10:11.444
Israel and a Palestinian state
are living side by side in peace.

159
00:10:11.445 --> 00:10:13.446
but it can still
all unravel so fast.

160
00:10:13.447 --> 00:10:14.907
Is that a threat?

161
00:10:15.490 --> 00:10:16.825
A threat?

162
00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:21.496
No. it's an invitation.

163
00:10:26.251 --> 00:10:28.462
I have to take that call. Okay?

164
00:10:31.131 --> 00:10:32.299
We need water.

165
00:10:34.676 --> 00:10:38.304
Mr. Bilton does not give
things away for free.

166
00:10:38.305 --> 00:10:42.392
so we need to be prepared for
what he will ask for in return.

167
00:10:43.143 --> 00:10:47.898
We have 3.000 reservations already. Did
I tell you who's doing the interiors?

168
00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:51.360
- You said Kanye. Still Kanye?
- Yeah! Yeah.

169
00:10:56.532 --> 00:10:58.282
I put together a schedule.

170
00:10:58.283 --> 00:11:01.327
From groundbreaking to
grand opening. nine months.

171
00:11:01.328 --> 00:11:02.746
A wise man once said.

172
00:11:03.247 --> 00:11:06.290
"What the bulldozers and dump
trucks do doesn't matter.

173
00:11:06.291 --> 00:11:08.501
so long as they do a lot of it."

174
00:11:08.502 --> 00:11:10.087
Can you believe these people?

175
00:11:10.963 --> 00:11:13.130
Hard to imagine they can march
with their heads up their asses.

176
00:11:13.131 --> 00:11:15.843
They say ice sheet in Greenland
is gonna break down the middle.

177
00:11:16.426 --> 00:11:19.429
- 79N ice sheet.
- Great. we'll build there next.

178
00:11:20.013 --> 00:11:22.682
They say three-meter sea level
rise by the end of the century.

179
00:11:22.683 --> 00:11:25.935
"They"? They also said the
same thing about Miami.

180
00:11:25.936 --> 00:11:28.271
All we did was make a fortune
retrofitting the buildings.

181
00:11:28.272 --> 00:11:30.940
And guess what? When it goes
up another couple of inches.

182
00:11:30.941 --> 00:11:33.776
we'll retro-fucking-fit again
and make even more money.

183
00:11:33.777 --> 00:11:36.070
Here's what you need to
know about global warmings.

184
00:11:36.071 --> 00:11:39.366
It will all go to shit at the end
of the century. One hundred percent.

185
00:11:40.117 --> 00:11:42.410
We'll be dead. We'll
have to miss it.

186
00:11:42.411 --> 00:11:45.454
but we'll be smiling in gold-plated
coffins designed by Kanye.

187
00:11:45.455 --> 00:11:47.249
So. let's focus on the now.

188
00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:51.252
Top of the World Casino is gonna
be the best casino in the world

189
00:11:51.253 --> 00:11:54.672
'cause there's
nothing else like it.

190
00:11:54.673 --> 00:11:57.216
Holy shit.

191
00:11:57.217 --> 00:11:58.552
Would you look at that?

192
00:11:59.595 --> 00:12:01.054
<i>If we go to 2...</i>

193
00:12:01.889 --> 00:12:04.099
Thank God. The trolls
finally shut her up.

194
00:12:12.399 --> 00:12:15.986
So then you're planning to keep it
empty for the foreseeable future?

195
00:12:16.570 --> 00:12:18.405
Never mind. Marshall. Forget it.

196
00:12:19.281 --> 00:12:21.532
I'll go ride a bike in
the gym or something.

197
00:12:21.533 --> 00:12:22.742
Yes. I understand.

198
00:12:22.743 --> 00:12:25.162
- At least there's no soot there.
- Yes. thank you.

199
00:12:25.662 --> 00:12:27.539
Okay. here's the deal.

200
00:12:28.123 --> 00:12:29.582
With the drought and the fires.

201
00:12:29.583 --> 00:12:32.336
they think that filling the
pool would be insensitive.

202
00:12:33.045 --> 00:12:34.295
They're worried
about the protests.

203
00:12:34.296 --> 00:12:36.881
They're using the pool water
to put out the forest fires?

204
00:12:36.882 --> 00:12:40.134
A Lebanese man set himself on
fire at the camp yesterday.

205
00:12:40.135 --> 00:12:41.969
Was he protesting
me swimming laps?

206
00:12:41.970 --> 00:12:43.721
I know you don't follow
this kind of stuff.

207
00:12:43.722 --> 00:12:48.684
but a lawyer. David Buckel. in
Brooklyn. did the same thing in 2018.

208
00:12:48.685 --> 00:12:51.270
Self-immolated to
protest climate change.

209
00:12:51.271 --> 00:12:54.065
- And did it work? Does it ever work?
- Define "work."

210
00:12:54.066 --> 00:12:58.027
It showed that the world is in
pain. That change is needed.

211
00:12:58.028 --> 00:13:02.032
The world is always in
pain. and it never changes.

212
00:13:02.699 --> 00:13:07.745
But to answer your question. work is
something you get paid for. A job.

213
00:13:07.746 --> 00:13:11.041
- And then there's how the world works.
- Well. I get paid in more than money.

214
00:13:13.377 --> 00:13:15.045
Dad. the people here need me.

215
00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:18.841
That's why I am planning
on staying in Israel.

216
00:13:19.675 --> 00:13:22.469
The people who are lighting
themselves on fire need you?

217
00:13:23.387 --> 00:13:27.056
Those people need psychiatric
help and fire extinguishers.

218
00:13:27.057 --> 00:13:29.642
- Why does nothing I say matter?
- You asked for my help.

219
00:13:29.643 --> 00:13:33.396
You said you wanted to be a rabbi.
so I paid for you to come here.

220
00:13:33.397 --> 00:13:35.815
- now you're a rabbi.
- Yes. I appreciate that.

221
00:13:35.816 --> 00:13:38.442
And then I set up the interview
at Temple Israel in Miami.

222
00:13:38.443 --> 00:13:40.486
Don't remember asking you
to do that one. but okay.

223
00:13:40.487 --> 00:13:44.574
I paid for the wood tick eradication in
their summer camp up in the Catskills

224
00:13:44.575 --> 00:13:46.576
when the Ellenberg
child got ill.

225
00:13:46.577 --> 00:13:47.869
I appreciate that too.

226
00:13:47.870 --> 00:13:50.080
And because of what
I did for them.

227
00:13:50.664 --> 00:13:54.543
they are now offering you
the position of Youth Rabbi.

228
00:13:56.461 --> 00:13:58.088
That's how the world works.

229
00:14:07.181 --> 00:14:09.515
<i>I want to speak to
my wife. please.</i>

